St Ninian lived in one of the chief epochs in the history os the Christian Church In the East‚ the Gregories, St Basil, and St. chrysostom, were toiling and suffering sor the saith, and in the West the destinies oi the Church were being moulded by no less Saints than Jerome, Ambrose‚ and Augustine. In Britain all was anarchy and barbarous warsare. The Roman legions were being withdrawn, and Britons,

Saxons, Picts, and Scots, were each fighting for their own hand.
